# Frontend Patterns

## State

Zustand store in `src/store/index.ts`. Settings persist to `localStorage` key `koi_settings`.

**Selectors:** subscribe to slices, not whole store:

```typescript
// ✅ Granular
const cpuUsage = useAppStore((s) => s.systemInfo?.cpu.usage ?? 0);

// ❌ Re-renders every telemetry tick
const { systemInfo } = useAppStore();
```

Chart history uses ring buffers (`store/historyRing.ts`):

```typescript
const cpuRing = useAppStore((s) => s.cpuHistoryRing);
const cpuHistory = useMemo(() => ringToArray(cpuRing), [cpuRing.seq]);
```

## API Layer

```typescript
// ✅ All IPC through services/api.ts
import { systemService } from '../services/api';
const info = await systemService.getSystemInfo();

// ❌ Don't scatter invoke() in components
```

## Telemetry (not polling for system metrics)

`useTelemetryPoller.ts`:
- Listens to Tauri events `telemetry-update` and `gaming-latency-update`
- DNS ping on interval only (skipped in Zen except min interval)
- Fallback polling if listen fails

Do **not** add a second system-info poll loop in `App.tsx`.

## Gaming latency UI

- Store: `gamingLatency: GamingLatencySnapshot` + `setGamingLatency()`
- `TelemetryGrid` — cell **Jeu** (Gamepad2 icon), not DNS ping
- Verdict badge is a **button** (`detailInteractive`) — toggles `GamingLatencyBreakdown` panel
- Panel hidden by default; close via **Fermer**, re-click badge, or **Escape**
- `GamingLatencyBreakdown` — 3 columns: Passerelle, Internet (`1.1.1.1`), Jitter (15 samples)
- Utils: `src/utils/gamingLatency.ts` — verdict colors, format ms, ring percent
- Active in dashboard (`StatsBar`) and Zen (`TelemetryGrid variant="embedded"`)

## Glass blur

- `src/utils/glassBlur.ts` — sync `html.no-blur` from `settings.enableGlassmorphicBlur`
- Init in `main.tsx` before React render; toggle in SettingsModal
- CSS: `globals.css` — `html:not(.no-blur)` enables glass; OFF disables all `[class*="backdrop-blur"]`

## Global toasts

```typescript
pushStatusToast('Message utilisateur', 'warning' | 'error' | 'success');
```

Rendered by `<StatusToast />` in `App.tsx` — `role="status"`, `aria-live="polite"`.

## Charts (Recharts lazy)

Import from `src/components/charts/` — not directly from `recharts` in widgets:

```typescript
import { SingleAreaChart } from '../charts';
// or DualAreaChart for network ↓/↑
```

Recharts loads async (chunk ~520 KB, budget 550 KB in CI).

## Constants

Shared constants live in `src/types/index.ts` (e.g. `POPULAR_DNS_SERVERS`, `DEFAULT_DNS_CHECKLIST`). Never duplicate magic strings across store/components.

## Widgets

Each widget in `src/components/widgets/` is self-contained, `React.memo` where applicable. Lazy-loaded from `App.tsx`. Export from `widgets/index.ts`.

## DNS Checklist

Server names must match `POPULAR_DNS_SERVERS[].name` exactly (e.g. `"Google DNS"`, not `"Google"`).
Use `normalizeDnsChecklist()` on load/save. Default auto mode: `DEFAULT_DNS_CHECKLIST` (4 servers).

## DNS Widget UX

- **Test auto** — reset to default checklist + immediate ping (`handleAutoDnsTest` in `App.tsx`)
- **Personnaliser** — opens `SettingsModal` on tab `network` via `initialTab` prop
- Badge/subtitle reflects auto vs custom count (`isAutoDnsChecklist`, `getDnsTestModeLabel`)

## StatsBar & TelemetryGrid

- `TelemetryGrid` in `src/components/common/TelemetryGrid.tsx` — shared metric cells (CPU, RAM, GPU, **Jeu**, Actif)
- `GamingLatencyBreakdown.tsx` — collapsible detail panel (passerelle / internet / jitter)
- `StatsBar` wraps `TelemetryGrid` for **dashboard only** (`App.tsx`: `{!zenMode && <StatsBar />}`)
- Zen: same grid embedded in `ZenClockWidget` via `<TelemetryGrid variant="embedded" />`
- Short labels: **Jeu** (latence multijoueur + badge verdict), **Actif** (uptime compact `Xh Xm`)
- DNS latency stays in `DnsWidget` only — do not mix with Jeu cell

## Settings Modal

- DNS checklist: two-line rows (`label` + `description` IP) in `CheckboxItem`
- `SettingsTabId` exported; `openSettings('network')` for DNS customization
- Toast in footer slot (no overlap with scroll content); warnings **5,5 s**, success **2,5 s**
- **Mode pilotes simplifiés:** défaut `true` ; désactivation → toast warning modal seul (~1–2 min rescan) ; description dynamique du switch
- **About tab:** `SlashTitle size="md"` with `key={aboutSlashKey}` to replay animation; copy professionnel (supervision Windows 11) + « Développé avec Tauri, React et Rust » + version footer

## Brand — SlashTitle

- `SlashTitle.tsx` — katana drop → cyan flash → split « Koi » / « Monitor »; props: `size`, `reducedMotion`, `gradient`, `className`
- `SplashSlashTitle.tsx` — splash wrapper (`size="lg"`)
- `TitleBar.tsx` — `SlashTitle size="sm"` when prop `playSlashAnimation`; static text during splash
- `SettingsModal.tsx` — About tab replays on each visit via incrementing `aboutSlashKey`
- Export from `components/common/index.ts`

## Splash Screen

- `SplashScreen.tsx` — orchestration séquentielle phases 0→4 (init / matériel / DNS / pilotes / prêt)
- Chaque phase : **durée min d'affichage** + condition backend (pas de skip visuel si réponse instantanée)
- Barre : interpolation lerp par phase, Framer Motion sur lignes et checkmarks
- Ready flags: `systemInfo`; DNS `dnsResults.length > 0 || dnsFetchAttempted`; pilotes `driversFetchSettled`
- Hard timeout **90 s** → `onComplete` anyway
- Respects `useReducedMotion()` (durées réduites)

## Drivers fetch & modes

- **Default:** `simplifiedMode: true` in store + settings reset
- Toggle simplified ↔ extended → `useEffect` calls `fetchDrivers(true)` in `App.tsx`
- Race guard: ignore stale responses if mode changed mid-scan
- **Simplified display:** `collapseEssentialDrivers()` in `DriversWidget` (GPU discret, Ethernet > Wi‑Fi, BT)
- **Extended:** liste complète backend ; toast warning **SettingsModal only** when disabling simplified (~1–2 min rescan)
- Refresh button: `getDrivers(simplifiedMode, force=true)`
- Backend cache TTL 5 min unless `force`
- UI: `DriverVersionCompare`, `EssentialVersionsSummary`, `hasDriverUpdate()` / segments diff
- **WU-first update UX:** when `update_source === 'windows_update'` → primary **« Ouvrir Windows Update »** (`driverService.openWindowsUpdate()`); vendor/catalog link secondary
- **Store-only** (`update_source === 'driver_store'`) → amber warning, vendor/catalog primary, **« Vérifier Windows Update »** secondary — no fake « Install update » button
- Helpers: `isWindowsUpdateSource`, `isDriverStoreOnlySource`, `getVendorUpdateLinkLabel` in `driverFormat.ts`
- Open URL: `isSafeExternalUrl()` before `openUrl`

## Chart Tooltips

```typescript
// chartData: index on X-axis, timestamp in payload
{ index, timestamp: item.timestamp, value: item.value }

// Use lazy chart components; tooltips via formatChartTooltipLabel
```

Use `formatChartTooltipLabel` from `chartUtils.ts` — reads `payload[0].payload.timestamp`. Do not use axis `label` for relative time.

## Network Widget

- Active connection: `getActiveConnection()` / `formatConnectionSubtitle()` from `src/utils/networkInterface.ts`
- Header icon: `Wifi` or `EthernetPort` based on backend `interface.kind`
- Layout: header badge (↓/↑) → chart → footer totals (same pattern as RAM/GPU)

## Drivers Widget

- Simplified mode: **3 essential rows** (post-collapse), `EssentialVersionsSummary` cards, compact rows
- Full mode: scrollable list, audio/storage/iGPU/Wi‑Fi included, expand overlay
- **Update actions (WU-first):** expand row → if MàJ dispo + WU source → blue **Ouvrir Windows Update** ; store-only → amber notice + OEM/catalog + **Vérifier Windows Update**
- No in-app driver install — user completes update via Windows Update or OEM site
- `NeonBentoCard` inner wrapper: `gap-4`, `flex-1 min-h-0` for correct flex overflow
- Network widget header: active adapter name via `getActiveNetworkAdapterName()` (`networkInterface.ts`)

## CPU Widget

- Per-core bars: `flex-1 min-w-0` on each bar — no horizontal scroll, adapts to core count (up to 32)
